# Implement Squad Filter in Daily Recap View

## Goal Description
The user wants to apply the squad filtering logic (present in [DailyMeetingView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#2526-2967)) to the [DailyRecapView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyRecapView.tsx#410-617). This will allow them to overview the progress of a specific subset of team members (a "squad") on the tasks they are working on, making it easier to track squad-specific daily movements without the noise of the entire team.

## Proposed Changes

### [src/components/dashboard/DailyRecapView.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyRecapView.tsx)
- **Imports**: Import [useRoles](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts#8-62), `ROLE_ORDER`, and [ValidRole](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts#6-7) from [useRoles.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts), and `Users` icon from `lucide-react`.
- **State**: Add a `selectedPersonsFilter` state (a `Set` of strings) to track selected squad members.
- **Hook**: Call [useRoles()](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts#8-62) to fetch the team roles.
- **Data Derivation**:
  - Extract all unique persons from `rawLogs`.
  - Sort these persons using `ROLE_ORDER` from [useRoles()](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useRoles.ts#8-62), identical to the logic in [DailyMeetingView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#2526-2967).
  - Create a `filteredMovementData` `useMemo` block. If `selectedPersonsFilter` is empty, it returns the original `movementData` (showing everyone by default). If there are personnel selected, it filters `movementData.personMovements` to only include the selected persons, and explicitly re-calculates the `Summary Stats` (total tasks moved forward, backward, etc.) for only those squad members.
- **UI Additions**:
  - Add the "Personnel Selector Row" (with the "Gradually form your squad" label) above the Summary Stats card.
  - Render a clickable row of buttons for each member in `sortedAllPersons`.
  - Use `filteredMovementData` instead of `movementData` for rendering the stats correctly and listing out the [PersonCard](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyRecapView.tsx#181-409)s.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Launch the local dev server.
2. Select a sprint that has activity.
3. Open the "Daily Recap" view in the dashboard.
4. Verify that the "Personnel Selector Row" appears at the top.
5. Click on one or more personnel to select them.
6. Observe that the "Summary Stats" and the "Person Cards" instantly update to only reflect the daily recap of those selected personnel.
7. Deselect all personnel and verify that it returns back to the global daily recap view.
8. Validate that the sorting of personnel follows the role hierarchy (Tester -> BE dev -> FE dev -> Team Leader -> Other).
